wiki.text:
'[[Interest]]' is any fee paid on borrowed capital. It may also refer to:

* Interest (emotion), the emotion prompting attention or curiosity **Relating to
  this, any hobby or other form of recreation or preference (in Social networks
  context) labeled "interest" - because a person feels an emotion of interest
  towards them **Romantically, individuals may be "interested" in others with
  sexual interest
* National interest or raison d'Ètat, the operant doctrines and ambitions
  of a state
* Self-interest, the ambitions of an individual
* Conflict of interest, the conflicting obligations of two or more parties in a
  dispute or trade
* The entitlement or right that someone has in or to property
* Returns (economics), the gain from the use of real capital, such as money
  earned on a loan or savings account
* Government interest, a legal concept describing the rationale of a government
  in enacting a law or regulation
